ZH: 他们试图抹杀我的声誉。
EN: They tried to assassinate my reputation.

ZH: 广告商们不惜代价地抹杀竞争对手。
EN: Advertisers spare no expense in eliminating their competitors.

ZH: 政府试图抹杀这些不利的新闻报道。
EN: The government tries to suppress these unfavorable news reports.

ZH: 这部电影不会被时间所抹杀。
EN: This movie will not be forgotten over time.

ZH: 他们企图用暴力来抹杀反对声音。
EN: They try to use violence to silence dissenting voices.

ZH: 媒体经常被指责试图抹杀真相。
EN: The media is often accused of trying to bury the truth.

ZH: 他的故事受到很多谣言的抹杀。
EN: His story has been heavily stifled by rumors.

ZH: 那些抹杀历史的企图是毫无意义的。
EN: Attempts to erase history are meaningless.

ZH: 这些证据会证明他试图抹杀事实的。
EN: This evidence will prove he tried to distort the facts.

ZH: 他们企图抹杀他的政治生涯。
EN: They seek to end his political career.

ZH: 这家公司一直试图抹杀竞争对手的创新能力。
EN: This company has been trying to suppress its competitors' innovation.

ZH: 那部作品永远不会被人们抹杀。
EN: That work will never be forgotten.

ZH: 抹杀真相是不道德的行为。
EN: Suppressing the truth is unethical.

ZH: 这种行为会导致故意抹杀他人的声誉。
EN: This behavior can lead to intentional smearing of others' reputations.

ZH: 这位总统试图抹杀关于他的负面新闻。
EN: The president tries to suppress negative news about him.

ZH: 报纸编辑试图抹杀这个丑闻。
EN: Newspaper editors try to bury this scandal.

ZH: 这家公司试图抹杀任何不赞成他们的声音。
EN: This company tries to shut down any voices that disagree with them.

ZH: 他们试图抹杀那位知名作家的声誉。
EN: They tried to ruin the reputation of that famous writer.

ZH: 那个政党曾试图抹杀对手的选情。
EN: That political party once tried to sabotage their opponent's campaign.

ZH: 这种做法试图抹杀平等和公正的原则。
EN: This approach seeks to erase the principles of equality and fairness.
